**End of Guide.**

> 💡 **When your client provides real certificates**: Delete `argocd-server-tls`, recreate with client's `.crt` and `.key`, restart NGINX. Everything else stays the same.
>
> 💡 **When adding dev / uat / prod clusters**: Use `argocd cluster add` after connecting kubectl to each cluster. They do NOT need to be on this same GKE cluster.
>
> 💡 **Correct install order recap**:
> 1. Phase 4 — NGINX Ingress Controller (internal LB first)
> 2. Phase 3 — TLS Secret (must exist before ArgoCD Helm install)
> 3. Phase 2 — `helm install argocd` (Ingress object created automatically)
> 4. Phase 5 — SSO
> 5. Phase 6 — RBAC
